name: THAT
bio: [('Beginning', 'She began taking cycling seriously at age 14. (vietnamnet.vn, 07 Apr 2018)'), ('Reason', 'Coach Ngo Quoc Tien spotted her talent for cycling while she was in the seventh grade of school, and invited her to compete for the An Giang provincial junior team in Vietnam. (vietnamnet.vn, 07 Apr 2018)'), ('Coach', 'Ngo Quoc Tien [national]; Alejandro Gonzalez Tablas [personal], ARG (uci.ch, 28 Apr 2018; vietnamnet.vn, 07 Apr 2018)'), ('Ambition', 'To win a gold medal at the 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia, and compete at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (vietnamplus.vn, 06 Jun 2018)'), ('Additional Information', "GeneralNATIONAL FIRSTShe became the first Vietnamese road cyclist to win a gold medal at the Asian championships when she claimed victory at the 2018 edition of the tournament in Naypyidaw, Myanmar. (vietnamplus.vn, 06 Jun 2018; SportsDeskOnline, 03 Jul 2018)SWISS TRAININGThe International Cycling Federation [UCI] gave her the chance to participate in a month-long training camp in June 2015 at the World Cycling Centre [WCC] in Aigle, Switzerland. The course encourages the development of cyclists from all over the world. In early 2018 she returned to the same training facility to prepare for that year's Asian Games in Indonesia.
